Controller
1. handle incoming requests nad building the response
2. business logic should not be handled here
@Controller


Repository
1. The nouns of the system
2. focused on persisting and interacting with the database
3. Usually a one-to-one mapping with the Objects
@Repository

Service Tier 
1. Verbs of our system
2. Where all of the business logic of the applciation should reside
3. Sometimes may have the same functions as Repository, but service tier should handle what to return in case of Null or if the constraints of the model are met, etc
whereas the repository tier only gets this information.
@Service